<p><b>Dr Ali Shariati</b> (<a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa"><b>علی شريعتی‎دکتر</b></span> ) (<a href="/wiki/November_23" title="November 23">November 23</a>, <a href="/wiki/1933" title="1933">1933</a> – 1977) was an <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iranian</a> <a href="/wiki/Sociology" title="Sociology">sociologist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Revolutionary" title="Revolutionary">revolutionary</a>, well known and respected for his work in the field of <a href="/wiki/Sociology_of_religion" title="Sociology of religion">sociology of religion</a>. He is known as one of the most original and influential Iranian social thinkers of the 20th century, as he was the ideologue of the <a href="/wiki/Iranian_Revolution" title="Iranian Revolution">Iranian Revolution</a>.</p>
